Text.SourceString: Here's something for my beloved. Not exactly a masterpiece, but I promise it comes from my heart.//<portrait=blushing>I hope you like it, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: Here's something for my beloved. Not exactly a masterpiece, but I promise it comes from my heart.//<portrait=blushing>I hope you like it, baby.

Text.SourceString: What's this, you ask? Well, a gift for you!//<portrait=happy>I woke up extra early today to make you this. Enjoy, my love!
Text.LocalizedString: What's this, you ask? Well, a gift for you!//<portrait=happy>I woke up extra early today to make you this. Enjoy, my love!

Text.SourceString: Good morning! Ready for another day of adventures?
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning! Ready for another day of adventures?

Text.SourceString: Goooood morning! What's the plan today, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Goooood morning! What's the plan today, babe?

Text.SourceString: Rise and shine, baby! Fall is so energizing here. Oh yeahhh!!!
Text.LocalizedString: Rise and shine, baby! Fall is so energizing here. Oh yeahhh!!!

Text.SourceString: So, what's on the agenda today, baby?//Have a good one, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: So, what's on the agenda today, baby?//Have a good one, okay?

Text.SourceString: How was your day, baby? You look like you could use a hug...or maybe a kiss?
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day, baby? You look like you could use a hug...or maybe a kiss?

Text.SourceString: Should we head to bed soon?//I'm getting tired, babe. My day was intense!
Text.LocalizedString: Should we head to bed soon?//I'm getting tired, babe. My day was intense!

Text.SourceString: Living with you definitely beats living with <NpcName>Charles</>.//<portrait=happy>Hahaha, just teasing, babe. Of course, it's not even comparable. PSYCHED!
Text.LocalizedString: Living with you definitely beats living with <NpcName>Charles</>.//<portrait=happy>Hahaha, just teasing, babe. Of course, it's not even comparable. PSYCHED!

Text.SourceString: Speaking of <NpcName>Charles</>, I should go and check up on him. He better not be watching TV alone again.
Text.LocalizedString: Speaking of <NpcName>Charles</>, I should go and check up on him. He better not be watching TV alone again.

Text.SourceString: This cabin is so cozy! I love it here.
Text.LocalizedString: This cabin is so cozy! I love it here.

Text.SourceString: I took a walk around this morning and let me just say, the farm looks amazing, babe.//<portrait=blushing>And who do we have to thank for that? Only the world's best farmer...you!
Text.LocalizedString: I took a walk around this morning and let me just say, the farm looks amazing, babe.//<portrait=blushing>And who do we have to thank for that? Only the world's best farmer...you!

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Millie</> was asking about a massive blue book. Have you seen it, baby?//<portrait=sad>I might've accidentally taken it home, I don't know...
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Millie</> was asking about a massive blue book. Have you seen it, baby?//<portrait=sad>I might've accidentally taken it home, I don't know...

Text.SourceString: The museum gig's alright. But it's not quite the same without my favorite distraction...you.//I'm a married man now, I can't be dusting bones 'til night falls. I don't want to.
Text.LocalizedString: The museum gig's alright. But it's not quite the same without my favorite distraction...you.//I'm a married man now, I can't be dusting bones 'til night falls. I don't want to.

Text.SourceString: Walking around town, baby?
Text.LocalizedString: Walking around town, baby?

Text.SourceString: I can use a break right now. Maybe I'll go and bug <NpcName>Charles</> for a bit... I kinda miss bugging that dude.
Text.LocalizedString: I can use a break right now. Maybe I'll go and bug <NpcName>Charles</> for a bit... I kinda miss bugging that dude.

Text.SourceString: You're welcome to stay as long as you want, babe.//That chair over there is comfy.
Text.LocalizedString: You're welcome to stay as long as you want, babe.//That chair over there is comfy.

Text.SourceString: Oh, they weren't kidding when they said love changes a man!//Being your husband has completely transformed me, in the most enticing ways.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, they weren't kidding when they said love changes a man!//Being your husband has completely transformed me, in the most enticing ways.

Text.SourceString: No more partying, <NpcName>Scott</>, enter doting hubsnad <NpcName>Scott</>...who occasionally still knows how to throw a good party.
Text.LocalizedString: No more partying, <NpcName>Scott</>, enter doting hubsnad <NpcName>Scott</>...who occasionally still knows how to throw a good party.

Text.SourceString: I've tried cleaning up the cabin.//What do you think? All neat and tidy now, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: I've tried cleaning up the cabin.//What do you think? All neat and tidy now, huh?

Text.SourceString: Gah, this rain... I think I'll just stay indoors today.//<portrait=happy>Should I build us a fort, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Gah, this rain... I think I'll just stay indoors today.//<portrait=happy>Should I build us a fort, babe?

Text.SourceString: You look amazing, baby. Gosh, I'm so lucky!//Just so you know! All my luck...used up trying to impress you. Worth it, though.
Text.LocalizedString: You look amazing, baby. Gosh, I'm so lucky!//Just so you know! All my luck...used up trying to impress you. Worth it, though.

Text.SourceString: Gah, this rain... I think I'll just stay indoors today.//<portrait=happy>Should I build us a fort, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Gah, this rain... I think I'll just stay indoors today.//<portrait=happy>Should I build us a fort, babe?

Text.SourceString: It's snowing outside. What do you say you and I...keep warm under the blanket today?
Text.LocalizedString: It's snowing outside. What do you say you and I...keep warm under the blanket today?

Text.SourceString: Wow...so beautiful...//The farm doesn't look so bad either.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow...so beautiful...//The farm doesn't look so bad either.

Text.SourceString: This <Italic>thing</> is so big, yeah, babe...our farm.//I can fit the whole museum here, I swear!
Text.LocalizedString: This <Italic>thing</> is so big, yeah, babe...our farm.//I can fit the whole museum here, I swear!

Text.SourceString: Hmm...should I go for a run? It could be a fun cardio session.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm...should I go for a run? It could be a fun cardio session.

Text.SourceString: Don't let me stop you, babe. But before that...//<portrait=blushing>Come here, you cute thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't let me stop you, babe. But before that...//<portrait=blushing>Come here, you cute thing.

Text.SourceString: Going mining? Do you need a spotter, babe?
Text.LocalizedString: Going mining? Do you need a spotter, babe?

Text.SourceString: Going here is so much more chill now with our house being so close to the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed><NpcName>Charles</>' house? Oof! Three hours one way.//Pain is what it was.
Text.LocalizedString: Going here is so much more chill now with our house being so close to the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed><NpcName>Charles</>' house? Oof! Three hours one way.//Pain is what it was.

Text.SourceString: Make sure you have your flashlight with you, baby. I don't want you to get hurt!
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure you have your flashlight with you, baby. I don't want you to get hurt!

Text.SourceString: Babe, listen... <NpcName>Charles</> always used to have falafel in the fridge, and I would sneak a bite or two. Ah, he didn't mind.//<portrait=concerned>But, uh, that sounds kinda mean. I should go apologize.
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, listen... <NpcName>Charles</> always used to have falafel in the fridge, and I would sneak a bite or two. Ah, he didn't mind.//<portrait=concerned>But, uh, that sounds kinda mean. I should go apologize.

Text.SourceString: I'm craving falafel. Should we make it?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm craving falafel. Should we make it?

Text.SourceString: This weather is perfect for some delicious egg custard for dessert. Mmm, yummy!
Text.LocalizedString: This weather is perfect for some delicious egg custard for dessert. Mmm, yummy!

Text.SourceString: Babe, have you seen my brush? I can't find it.
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, have you seen my brush? I can't find it.

Text.SourceString: Babe, I can't find my gloves. I want to wear them for Winter... Are they in your drawer?//<portrait=sad>Can you help me look for them later? Pleaseee?
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, I can't find my gloves. I want to wear them for Winter... Are they in your drawer?//<portrait=sad>Can you help me look for them later? Pleaseee?

Text.SourceString: Babe, do you know where my sunnies are...//<portrait=happy>Oh, never mind, I'm wearing them.
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, do you know where my sunnies are...//<portrait=happy>Oh, never mind, I'm wearing them.

Text.SourceString: Time to get back to work.//<portrait=happy>Monday, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Time to get back to work.//<portrait=happy>Monday, huh?

Text.SourceString: I don’t miss the city as much as I thought I would.//<portrait=concerned>There’s not much there for me to miss.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t miss the city as much as I thought I would.//<portrait=concerned>There’s not much there for me to miss.

Text.SourceString: I find all kinds of things in the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed>Some of them are very…weird.
Text.LocalizedString: I find all kinds of things in the cavern.//<portrait=annoyed>Some of them are very…weird.

Text.SourceString: On my second cup of tea today.//Now I'm all jittery. Caffeine powers activate!
Text.LocalizedString: On my second cup of tea today.//Now I'm all jittery. Caffeine powers activate!

Text.SourceString: When I’m cleaning artifacts, I try not to use too much chemical solution because I’m afraid it might damage them.
Text.LocalizedString: When I’m cleaning artifacts, I try not to use too much chemical solution because I’m afraid it might damage them.

Text.SourceString: But some is needed to break through the crust.//So there’s a careful balance we archeologists have to strike.
Text.LocalizedString: But some is needed to break through the crust.//So there’s a careful balance we archeologists have to strike.

Text.SourceString: I think I used too much hair gel today.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I used too much hair gel today.

Text.SourceString: Still looks good, though, so I’m not stressed about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Still looks good, though, so I’m not stressed about it.

Text.SourceString: The cavern in the forest is surprisingly deep.//There are all kinds of things buried down there.
Text.LocalizedString: The cavern in the forest is surprisingly deep.//There are all kinds of things buried down there.

Text.SourceString: If you’re lucky, you can even find weapons.//<portrait=concerned>Now, how they got there in the first place, nobody knows…
Text.LocalizedString: If you’re lucky, you can even find weapons.//<portrait=concerned>Now, how they got there in the first place, nobody knows…

Text.SourceString: I like working in the field as much as I do in the museum. There are a lot of places to dig.
Text.LocalizedString: I like working in the field as much as I do in the museum. There are a lot of places to dig.

Text.SourceString: Technically, I’m working today. I’m just not in the office.
Text.LocalizedString: Technically, I’m working today. I’m just not in the office.

Text.SourceString: I'm more of a roguish, on-the-go kind of worker today, you know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm more of a roguish, on-the-go kind of worker today, you know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: I keep stumbling upon these mind-boggling artifacts. Like, seriously, I once found a gigantic spoon at sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep stumbling upon these mind-boggling artifacts. Like, seriously, I once found a gigantic spoon at sea.

Text.SourceString: I'm talking a spoon as big as my head! What on earth is going on?//<portrait=normal>Are there giant mermaids with massive cutlery roaming around?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm talking a spoon as big as my head! What on earth is going on?//<portrait=normal>Are there giant mermaids with massive cutlery roaming around?

Text.SourceString: Another Spring…another year begins…another birthday season for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Another Spring…another year begins…another birthday season for me.

Text.SourceString: I’m getting back into my routine now… I can get to the cavern more easily.//The path to the forest isn’t so slippery now the snow’s melted.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m getting back into my routine now… I can get to the cavern more easily.//The path to the forest isn’t so slippery now the snow’s melted.

Text.SourceString: I see more and more people outdoors now the weather is <Italic>livable</> again…
Text.LocalizedString: I see more and more people outdoors now the weather is <Italic>livable</> again…

Text.SourceString: I did a new workout regimen for Winter.//It was a fifteen-day thing. Can you tell? I'm all about those toned muscles now, baby.
Text.LocalizedString: I did a new workout regimen for Winter.//It was a fifteen-day thing. Can you tell? I'm all about those toned muscles now, baby.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if it’s the Summer heat, or… I don’t know what, but one of the shafts in the cavern is so hot lately.//Weird thing is it’s just that one, though… Like something is flaming inside.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if it’s the Summer heat, or… I don’t know what, but one of the shafts in the cavern is so hot lately.//Weird thing is it’s just that one, though… Like something is flaming inside.

Text.SourceString: My cavern-o-meter isn’t a fancy one, but it picked up the different temperatures in the shafts.//It’s weird. You see, temperatures down there don’t usually change like that.//Even in Summer!
Text.LocalizedString: My cavern-o-meter isn’t a fancy one, but it picked up the different temperatures in the shafts.//It’s weird. You see, temperatures down there don’t usually change like that.//Even in Summer!

Text.SourceString: Better soak up the last of that Summer sun, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Better soak up the last of that Summer sun, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I’m ready to soak up the sun!//<portrait=annoyed>And if you’re going to remind me about sunscreen, don’t worry. I get an earful every day from <NPCName>Charles</>.//Sunscreen, sunscreen, sunscreen…
Text.LocalizedString: I’m ready to soak up the sun!//<portrait=annoyed>And if you’re going to remind me about sunscreen, don’t worry. I get an earful every day from <NPCName>Charles</>.//Sunscreen, sunscreen, sunscreen…

Text.SourceString: Thinking of playing volleyball at the beach tomorrow. Wonder if anyone will be up for a match.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Chaem</> maybe? Or…//<portrait=normal>Will you be there?
Text.LocalizedString: Thinking of playing volleyball at the beach tomorrow. Wonder if anyone will be up for a match.//<portrait=concerned><NPCName>Chaem</> maybe? Or…//<portrait=normal>Will you be there?

Text.SourceString: I don’t mind the walk to the forest, especially on nice Summer days.//I get to see what <NPCName>Kira's</> planting, see what <NPCName>Jack's</> up to. All that stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t mind the walk to the forest, especially on nice Summer days.//I get to see what <NPCName>Kira's</> planting, see what <NPCName>Jack's</> up to. All that stuff.

Text.SourceString: Don’t you think jazz is the perfect background music for Fall?//Love jazz. It's smooth, it's classy, it's everything you need to embrace the cozy vibes.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t you think jazz is the perfect background music for Fall?//Love jazz. It's smooth, it's classy, it's everything you need to embrace the cozy vibes.

Text.SourceString: The ground in Fall feels a bit different from other seasons. That’s the first thing I notice, usually.//That and the leaves changing color.
Text.LocalizedString: The ground in Fall feels a bit different from other seasons. That’s the first thing I notice, usually.//That and the leaves changing color.

Text.SourceString: There are so many mushrooms in the forest now.//I don’t do that kind of thing, but if you like them, you should go forage around.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many mushrooms in the forest now.//I don’t do that kind of thing, but if you like them, you should go forage around.

Text.SourceString: *singing* Mmm shoopadoo wawa hmmmm~
Text.LocalizedString: *singing* Mmm shoopadoo wawa hmmmm~

Text.SourceString: Oh, sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I just had this jazz melody in my head.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, sorry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I just had this jazz melody in my head.

Text.SourceString: The air in the cavern is much warmer than outside, especially with the snow everywhere.//Rocks are great insulators. Caverns stay relatively the same temperature year round.
Text.LocalizedString: The air in the cavern is much warmer than outside, especially with the snow everywhere.//Rocks are great insulators. Caverns stay relatively the same temperature year round.

Text.SourceString: Cool when it’s Summer, warm in Winter… That sort of thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Cool when it’s Summer, warm in Winter… That sort of thing.

Text.SourceString: Remember to be extra careful walking to the forest. Icy path and all.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember to be extra careful walking to the forest. Icy path and all.

Text.SourceString: It’s Winter again. Time does fly when you’re having fun!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Winter again. Time does fly when you’re having fun!

Text.SourceString: Lots of animals hibernate in Winter… Ever wonder which ones hibernate in the caverns?
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of animals hibernate in Winter… Ever wonder which ones hibernate in the caverns?

Text.SourceString: Having breakfast outdoors is different in Winter… Do not recommend it.
Text.LocalizedString: Having breakfast outdoors is different in Winter… Do not recommend it.

Text.SourceString: Have you started working on our farm yet, baby?//There must be a lot of weeding to do. Can I help?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you started working on our farm yet, baby?//There must be a lot of weeding to do. Can I help?

Text.SourceString: I’m so sore. I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so sore. I’ve been lifting a lot lately.

Text.SourceString: How’s your Summer so far?
Text.LocalizedString: How’s your Summer so far?

Text.SourceString: I woke up yesterday with bug bites on my ankles.
Text.LocalizedString: I woke up yesterday with bug bites on my ankles.

Text.SourceString: I grew up fishing with my dad. We would wake up early on the weekend, around 4 am, and catch a boat to go fishing at sea.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up fishing with my dad. We would wake up early on the weekend, around 4 am, and catch a boat to go fishing at sea.

Text.SourceString: We’d bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset. Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner. We’d cook up our catch the next day.
Text.LocalizedString: We’d bring our lunches out and sail home at sunset. Then Dad and I would stop by a ramen place on the way home for dinner. We’d cook up our catch the next day.

Text.SourceString: I feel sticky… Yuck.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel sticky… Yuck.

Text.SourceString: Oh, I’m not too worried about mosquitoes. They prefer one particular blood type over the other.//And mine happens to be “the other.”
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, I’m not too worried about mosquitoes. They prefer one particular blood type over the other.//And mine happens to be “the other.”

Text.SourceString: The cavern is wild, though. The mosquitos attack no matter what… Maybe because there are no other targets down there.
Text.LocalizedString: The cavern is wild, though. The mosquitos attack no matter what… Maybe because there are no other targets down there.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how long my hair can survive in this heat.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how long my hair can survive in this heat.

Text.SourceString: I have these holes in my shoes that keep my feet nice and cool.
Text.LocalizedString: I have these holes in my shoes that keep my feet nice and cool.

Text.SourceString: Have you got those holes in your shoes?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you got those holes in your shoes?

Text.SourceString: Not many plants can survive the Winter snow. I hope it means less work for you, babe.
Text.LocalizedString: Not many plants can survive the Winter snow. I hope it means less work for you, babe.

Text.SourceString: Maybe we can spend Winter cuddling instead.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe we can spend Winter cuddling instead.

Text.SourceString: In less than three weeks, it’ll be the New Year. I’m psyched!
Text.LocalizedString: In less than three weeks, it’ll be the New Year. I’m psyched!

Text.SourceString: I need to make sure to stock up on tea.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to make sure to stock up on tea.

Text.SourceString: The thunder woke me up at two o’clock this morning!
Text.LocalizedString: The thunder woke me up at two o’clock this morning!

Text.SourceString: I couldn’t go back to bed after that.
Text.LocalizedString: I couldn’t go back to bed after that.

Text.SourceString: Another year has passed.
Text.LocalizedString: Another year has passed.

Text.SourceString: There are things I wish I’d handled differently.
Text.LocalizedString: There are things I wish I’d handled differently.

Text.SourceString: Friends are important to me.//So I try my best to set aside some time every week to keep up with them.
Text.LocalizedString: Friends are important to me.//So I try my best to set aside some time every week to keep up with them.

Text.SourceString: Some of the artifacts here are ones I found.//My little contribution to the field I'm so passionate about.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of the artifacts here are ones I found.//My little contribution to the field I'm so passionate about.

Text.SourceString: Call it being part of history, yeah? Making my mark.
Text.LocalizedString: Call it being part of history, yeah? Making my mark.

Text.SourceString: I’m so sore… I’ve been lifting a lot lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so sore… I’ve been lifting a lot lately.

Text.SourceString: A nice hot bath sounds excellent right about now. You should join me baby.
Text.LocalizedString: A nice hot bath sounds excellent right about now. You should join me baby.

Text.SourceString: Growing old? Nah, doesn't stress me out anymore.//<portrait=blushing>I have you now, baby. I'm looking forward to growing old with you.
Text.LocalizedString: Growing old? Nah, doesn't stress me out anymore.//<portrait=blushing>I have you now, baby. I'm looking forward to growing old with you.

Text.SourceString: Are you out to go fishing too, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you out to go fishing too, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: One time, I caught myself a couple of pink snappers within ten minutes of each other.//I’m still amazed about it to this day.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, I caught myself a couple of pink snappers within ten minutes of each other.//I’m still amazed about it to this day.

Text.SourceString: Fingers crossed, <PlayerName>$player</>. It might happen again!
Text.LocalizedString: Fingers crossed, <PlayerName>$player</>. It might happen again!

Text.SourceString: I smell like the ocean.
Text.LocalizedString: I smell like the ocean.

Text.SourceString: A hint of saltiness that's hard to resist.//Care for a taste?
Text.LocalizedString: A hint of saltiness that's hard to resist.//Care for a taste?

Text.SourceString: Did you bring vitamins with you?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you bring vitamins with you?

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll go out for a bit and have a snack by the creek.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll go out for a bit and have a snack by the creek.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I didn’t get anything valuable today.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I didn’t get anything valuable today.

Text.SourceString: But at least I got a good workout in the cavern.
Text.LocalizedString: But at least I got a good workout in the cavern.

Text.SourceString: This is a nice spot for a lunch break.//I might cool my feet in the creek afterward.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a nice spot for a lunch break.//I might cool my feet in the creek afterward.

Text.SourceString: Yikes! Something came at me in the dark, so I ran as fast as I could.
Text.LocalizedString: Yikes! Something came at me in the dark, so I ran as fast as I could.

Text.SourceString: I’m still trying to catch my breath, uh, yeah...
Text.LocalizedString: I’m still trying to catch my breath, uh, yeah...

Text.SourceString: There’s so much cool stuff in the cavern, but no one likes to get their hands dirty down there.//It’s too bad.//<portrait=happy>More for me, I guess!
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so much cool stuff in the cavern, but no one likes to get their hands dirty down there.//It’s too bad.//<portrait=happy>More for me, I guess!

Text.SourceString: They should play more jazz at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It would give it that classy, ritzy feel. Know what I mean?
Text.LocalizedString: They should play more jazz at the Tavern.//<portrait=happy>It would give it that classy, ritzy feel. Know what I mean?

Text.SourceString: Picture us...you and me...sipping cocktails, swaying to the smooth tunes... Now that's my kind of evening.
Text.LocalizedString: Picture us...you and me...sipping cocktails, swaying to the smooth tunes... Now that's my kind of evening.

Text.SourceString: There’s nothing better than okra and turnips. They remind me of my mom’s cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s nothing better than okra and turnips. They remind me of my mom’s cooking.

Text.SourceString: Mom always made sure the fridge was stocked with food and snacks and whatever.//<portrait=happy>What a champ!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom always made sure the fridge was stocked with food and snacks and whatever.//<portrait=happy>What a champ!

Text.SourceString: I don’t really miss the city.//The sunsets here are much nicer… In the city, all the buildings block your view of the sky.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really miss the city.//The sunsets here are much nicer… In the city, all the buildings block your view of the sky.

Text.SourceString: The Spring rains erode the cavern a little more each year. Over time, more artifacts and gems are uncovered.//<portrait=happy>Don’t quote me on that, though. That’s just my theory!
Text.LocalizedString: The Spring rains erode the cavern a little more each year. Over time, more artifacts and gems are uncovered.//<portrait=happy>Don’t quote me on that, though. That’s just my theory!

Text.SourceString: There are bad things about rain too, if you think about it.//<portrait=annoyed>For one, if you don’t get to the artifacts in time, the rain can give them a beating. Heck, even destroy them!//<portrait=happy>That’s also my theory.
Text.LocalizedString: There are bad things about rain too, if you think about it.//<portrait=annoyed>For one, if you don’t get to the artifacts in time, the rain can give them a beating. Heck, even destroy them!//<portrait=happy>That’s also my theory.

Text.SourceString: The one thing Coral Island has over the city is beach life.//There’s nothing like blasting a cannonball right into the waves.
Text.LocalizedString: The one thing Coral Island has over the city is beach life.//There’s nothing like blasting a cannonball right into the waves.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer.//Sure feels like Winter was just a couple of days ago.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s already Summer.//Sure feels like Winter was just a couple of days ago.

Text.SourceString: Fall is the time of year when people get into relationships, right?//So they can meet each other’s families during the holidays.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is the time of year when people get into relationships, right?//So they can meet each other’s families during the holidays.

Text.SourceString: Not for this married guy right here! Every season is relationship season.
Text.LocalizedString: Not for this married guy right here! Every season is relationship season.

Text.SourceString: Am I ready for Winter?//<portrait=normal>Hmm… I guess so.
Text.LocalizedString: Am I ready for Winter?//<portrait=normal>Hmm… I guess so.

Text.SourceString: Is it just me, or does Winter seem like the quietest season?//<portrait=normal>Someone needs to turn up the volume out here.
Text.LocalizedString: Is it just me, or does Winter seem like the quietest season?//<portrait=normal>Someone needs to turn up the volume out here.

Text.SourceString: Winter just seems so depressing to me. It’s dark and cold, and everything is dead.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter just seems so depressing to me. It’s dark and cold, and everything is dead.

Text.SourceString: Give me sunshine and a swimsuit any day over snow and a parka.
Text.LocalizedString: Give me sunshine and a swimsuit any day over snow and a parka.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll actually have to wear long pants when I go digging now.//The cavern’s all right this time of year, but it’s freezing on the walk over there.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll actually have to wear long pants when I go digging now.//The cavern’s all right this time of year, but it’s freezing on the walk over there.

Text.SourceString: Everyone on the island seems to like Winter the most, but I’m really more of a Summer guy.//<portrait=happy>What’s not to love about sweating it out on the beach?
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone on the island seems to like Winter the most, but I’m really more of a Summer guy.//<portrait=happy>What’s not to love about sweating it out on the beach?

Text.SourceString: Rain isn’t too bad. It makes everything look hazy…like a dream.//<portrait=concerned>It <Italic>does</> make my hair go all frizzy, though. It’s like I’m stuck in a bad ’80s music video.
Text.LocalizedString: Rain isn’t too bad. It makes everything look hazy…like a dream.//<portrait=concerned>It <Italic>does</> make my hair go all frizzy, though. It’s like I’m stuck in a bad ’80s music video.

Text.SourceString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Text.LocalizedString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?

Text.SourceString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?
Text.LocalizedString: Jeez, I can’t even get fresh air out here without taking in a mouthful of water.//<portrait=concerned>Is this how fish feel?

Text.SourceString: Hello? Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>? I can hear you, but I can’t see through all this rain!
Text.LocalizedString: Hello? Is that you, <PlayerName>$player</>? I can hear you, but I can’t see through all this rain!

Text.SourceString: The rain is really coming down out there. I hope it doesn’t ruin your plans for the day.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain is really coming down out there. I hope it doesn’t ruin your plans for the day.

Text.SourceString: I can’t believe it’s raining again. I thought we were supposed to have nice weather this week.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t believe it’s raining again. I thought we were supposed to have nice weather this week.

Text.SourceString: Rainy days make me feel like curling up with some tea and reading a book… And I don’t even like to read.//<portrait=happy>Weird, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Rainy days make me feel like curling up with some tea and reading a book… And I don’t even like to read.//<portrait=happy>Weird, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: Snow day!
Text.LocalizedString: Snow day!

Text.SourceString: The snow makes my hair go flat.//Do you think it looks flat?//<portrait=normal>Phew! Don’t worry about yours. Your hair always looks great!
Text.LocalizedString: The snow makes my hair go flat.//Do you think it looks flat?//<portrait=normal>Phew! Don’t worry about yours. Your hair always looks great!

Text.SourceString: Is there any way to tell if the big fish are out today? They should do a Coral Island fish forecast.
Text.LocalizedString: Is there any way to tell if the big fish are out today? They should do a Coral Island fish forecast.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, I’d rather be lifting weights or jogging, but yoga’s cool too.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, I’d rather be lifting weights or jogging, but yoga’s cool too.

Text.SourceString: Anything that gets me moving is cool with me.
Text.LocalizedString: Anything that gets me moving is cool with me.

Text.SourceString: Strange, there was a kite just outside our window this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Strange, there was a kite just outside our window this morning.

Text.SourceString: I haven’t seen anyone flying a kite in ages.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen anyone flying a kite in ages.

Text.SourceString: Bleh… I had some fresh veggies yesterday, and I can still taste the bitter flavor on my tongue.//<portrait=annoyed>Vegetables aren’t for me. So when I go down in the cavern, I usually just pack vitamins from the clinic.
Text.LocalizedString: Bleh… I had some fresh veggies yesterday, and I can still taste the bitter flavor on my tongue.//<portrait=annoyed>Vegetables aren’t for me. So when I go down in the cavern, I usually just pack vitamins from the clinic.

Text.SourceString: Okra’s all right, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Okra’s all right, though.

Text.SourceString: I’ve thought about changing my hair a couple of times, but I have no idea how to settle on a style.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve thought about changing my hair a couple of times, but I have no idea how to settle on a style.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I could try a buzz cut like <NpcName>Sam</>.//<portrait=normal>It looks good on him, don’t you think? And I’d save a ton on hair gel.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I could try a buzz cut like <NpcName>Sam</>.//<portrait=normal>It looks good on him, don’t you think? And I’d save a ton on hair gel.

Text.SourceString: I should really cut my hair, huh?//It seems like the Summer heat bewitches my hair and makes it grow extra fast.
Text.LocalizedString: I should really cut my hair, huh?//It seems like the Summer heat bewitches my hair and makes it grow extra fast.

Text.SourceString: I think I ate something bad this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I ate something bad this morning.

Text.SourceString: My stomach won’t stop growling. Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: My stomach won’t stop growling. Hmm…

Text.SourceString: The system at the museum was down the other day. Thankfully, <NpcName>Lily</> was able to stop by and help out.
Text.LocalizedString: The system at the museum was down the other day. Thankfully, <NpcName>Lily</> was able to stop by and help out.

Text.SourceString: I could have tried to fix it, I guess.//<portrait=happy>But I didn’t know how… Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I could have tried to fix it, I guess.//<portrait=happy>But I didn’t know how… Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: I’m liking that shirt on you, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m liking that shirt on you, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’d look good in that color too. I might try it out.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’d look good in that color too. I might try it out.

Text.SourceString: The rain makes everything feel so fresh and clean. I love the smell of wet pavement and leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: The rain makes everything feel so fresh and clean. I love the smell of wet pavement and leaves.

Text.SourceString: It seems like the perfect weather for snuggling, don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: It seems like the perfect weather for snuggling, don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Don’t get sick, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t get sick, okay?

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, I wish I’d been born a hundred years ago, when men still wore suits everywhere and jazz was the big thing.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, I wish I’d been born a hundred years ago, when men still wore suits everywhere and jazz was the big thing.

Text.SourceString: Technology is cool and all, but nothing beats a good big-band show.
Text.LocalizedString: Technology is cool and all, but nothing beats a good big-band show.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice and toasty here. In the mood for something hot?//<portrait=blushing>To drink, I mean!
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice and toasty here. In the mood for something hot?//<portrait=blushing>To drink, I mean!

Text.SourceString: Everyone stay close in here so we can keep warm!//<portrait=blushing>And also so I don’t have to shout.
Text.LocalizedString: Everyone stay close in here so we can keep warm!//<portrait=blushing>And also so I don’t have to shout.

Text.SourceString: Speaking of… You smell really nice up close, <PlayerName>$player</>.//This is the best part about snowy days…
Text.LocalizedString: Speaking of… You smell really nice up close, <PlayerName>$player</>.//This is the best part about snowy days…

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’ll ever be a fan of cold Winters, but I guess that’s just how it goes. Some people love them, and some people don’t.//<portrait=blushing>I wouldn’t mind if…if someone had to keep my hands warm.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’ll ever be a fan of cold Winters, but I guess that’s just how it goes. Some people love them, and some people don’t.//<portrait=blushing>I wouldn’t mind if…if someone had to keep my hands warm.

Text.SourceString: This would be an excellent place for a date, you know.//Just you, me, and thousands of years of history all around us.
Text.LocalizedString: This would be an excellent place for a date, you know.//Just you, me, and thousands of years of history all around us.

Text.SourceString: I always have a great time here, but we need some new stuff on the menu.//Maybe I should tell <NPCName>Frank</> about that okra and turnip drink I came up with.
Text.LocalizedString: I always have a great time here, but we need some new stuff on the menu.//Maybe I should tell <NPCName>Frank</> about that okra and turnip drink I came up with.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know about you, but I’m counting down the days until Summer is finally here.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know about you, but I’m counting down the days until Summer is finally here.

Text.SourceString: The weather is so dreary and depressing today. It’s just not my thing.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is so dreary and depressing today. It’s just not my thing.
